fielddes: Unique ID given to the Officer. An Officer is a person or company that has some form of control over a Legal Entity.
Unique ID assigned by BQ to the Organization.

Primary name of the Organization, derived from multiple sources including the IRS, Dept. of Labor, SEC, SBA, and local jurisdictions. A waterfall is in place to pick the Organization's primary name, with preference given to IRS related sources.
TICKER of the Organization if it is publicly listed.

Link to the Organization's primary website. A company's website is not usually included in the regulatory filings, but BQ uses alternative methods to identify these links, which may result in occasional inaccuracies.
ID of the Legal Entity over which the Officer has control.
Name of the Legal Entity over which the Officer has control.
Unique number issued by the jurisdiction with which the Legal Entity is registered.
Jurisdiction code (2-digit state name) in which the Legal Entity is registered, typically with the Secretary of State.
ID of the Legal Entity that the Officer represents.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Legal Entity that the Officer controls is registered as an Agent and 0 otherwise.
ID of the Organization associated with the Legal Entity that the Officer represents.
Full name of the Officer.
First name of the Officer.
Last name of the Officer.
Middle name of the Officer.
Middle initial of the Officer.
Rank of the Primary legal position held by the Officer.
Rank of the Secondary position held by the Officer.
Rank of the Tertiary position held by the Officer.
Remaining ranks of all other positions held by the Officer, in order of importance.
Primary legal position held by the Officer. There are 24 distinct Officer positions.
Secondary legal position held by the Officer. There are 24 distinct Officer positions.
Tertiary legal position held by the Officer. There are 24 distinct Officer positions.
Any other additional legal positions held by the Officer. There are 24 distinct Officer positions.
Count of the number of distinct legal positions held by the Officer. There are 24 distinct Officer legal positions.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of CFO and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of Assistant CFO and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of Officer and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of Partner and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of Real Property and 0 otherwise. Primarily aplicable in the context of real estate.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of Incorporator and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the position of any Other Position and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the position of Applicant and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of Chairman and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of CEO and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of Managing member and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of Treasurer and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of Secretary and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of General Partner and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of Member and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of Agent and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of President and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of COO and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the position of Manager and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer is the related company and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of Executive Officer and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of GM and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of Director and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of Assistant Secretary and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of Assistant Treasurer and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer holds the legal position of VP and 0 otherwise.
This lists all distinct legal positions held by the Officer.
Classification system for the Officer based on whether the Officer is a person or a company.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer's address is valid based on USPS address verification and 0 otherwise.
First line of the Officer's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Second line of the Officer's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
City name of the Officer's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
State's abbrivated name of the Officer's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
State name of the Officer's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
County-level Federal Information Processing Standard (FIPS) Code of the Officer's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
County name of the Officer's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
County of the Officer's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
5-digit zip code of the Officer's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
9-Digit zip code of the Officer's. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Zip code classification of the Officer's address stating whether it is a P.O. Box or not. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Latitute of the Officer's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Longitude of the Organization's headquarters address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Classification that indicates whether the Officer's address is Match-Mailable or Non-Mailable based on USPS reporting.
RDI indicates whether the Officer's address is Residential, Commercial, P.O. Box or Unknown based on USPS reporting.
Name of the Core-Based Statistical Area (CBSA) which identifies the Metropolitan Statistical Area or Micropolitan Statistical Area in which the Officer's address lies according to USPS.

The Core-Based Statistical Area (CBSA) is a 5-digit numeric code which identifies the Metropolitan Statistical Area or Micropolitan Statistical Area in which the Officer's address lies according to USPS.
Metro or Micro Type classification of the Core-Based Statistical Area (CBSA) in which the Officer's address lies according to USPS.
Numerical portion (if any) of the 2nd line of the Officer's address, such as a unit or suite number. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Indicator that states "Yes" if the Officer's address is verified to be deliverable based on the Delivery Point Validation Process of USPS.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Officer's address is the "default" address for a building ( i.e., the main lobby) and 0 otherwise. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Congressional District Code of the Officer's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
